The paper focuses on developing a reliable communication system for unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in the context of maritime search and rescue (SAR). The paper discusses the use of Long Term Evolution (LTE) technology and resource-guaranteed scheduling to mitigate the challenges of providing reliable communication over long distances. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of an autopilot system, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for real-time command and control, which could fall under the category of cyber-security (cs.CR) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of an open-source LTE stack and the evaluation of the system, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
